article.headline: Valparaiso 91, Chicago St. 76
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Shawn Huff scored 25 points and Urule Igbavboa recorded a triple-double as Valparaiso beat Chicago State 91-76 Monday night. Igbavboa had 18 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists for the Crusaders (13-11), who shot nearly 77 percent in the second half to build on a 39-33 halftime lead and finish at better than 67 percent for the game. Chicago State's Royce Parran led all scorers with 33 points on 11-of-16 shooting from the field and 8-of-12 shooting from the free throw line. The Cougars (8-19) scored 28 points off Valparaiso turnovers, compared with 15 points off turnovers for the Crusaders, but were outrebounded 35-22 for the game. Huff was 9-of-13 from the floor, including three 3-pointers. Samuel Haanpaa added 17 points and was 4-of-5 from behind the arc for Valparaiso. Brandon McPherson chipped in 13 points for the Crusaders.
